              the perception of agency over electrically-actuated movements
              using human-in-the-loop Bayesian optimization. Using this
              paradigm while subjects undergo EEG recording, we show that early
              (sensorimotor) and late (post-consciousness) neural patterns,
              which show distinct temporal dynamics, both predict illusory SoA
