  author    = "Economidou, Eleni and Hengeveld, Bart",
  abstract  = "Computation is increasingly seen as a design material, finding
               its way into once mundane objects, surfaces and spaces. As such,
               demonstrations of the convergence of architectural elements and
               interactive systems are becoming commonplace in both research
               and industry. While eXtended Reality (XR) and projection mapping
               technologies seem to be ubiquitous in this field, shape-changing
               interfaces are under-represented. In this case study we explore
               the domain of shape-changing thresholds in the form of an
               interactive door panel. Corresponding to conditions of space
